extravaganza
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:[Spec. and joc. use of extravaganza--> a composition, literary, musical, of an extravagant or fantastic character.] The traditional name of the Victoria University (College) student revue, beginning c1907 with `The Golden Calf'.
Origin:
